# PROJECT NAME:

SalesHub – AI-Powered Telecom Due Diligence & Revenue Intelligence Engine

==============================================================================

1. PROJECT EXPLANATION
   ==============================================================================

SalesHub is an enterprise-grade automation system designed to perform deep telecom corporate due diligence combined with live revenue intelligence.

Unlike simple company lookup tools, SalesHub integrates:

* Regulatory data (FCC, RMD, FRN)
* API-based compliance verification
* Revenue analytics
* Interconnect intelligence
* AI-powered risk assessment
* Tier-based credit recommendations
* Tailored business opportunity mapping

The system is built entirely in n8n and exposed via a Webhook endpoint. It accepts:

* Our Company Name
* Target Company Name
* Target Company Website URL

SalesHub then automatically:

1. Extracts official company identity from website
2. Pulls FCC and RMD data via API
3. Normalizes regulatory records
4. Merges compliance + API intelligence
5. Generates a full Due Diligence report using an advanced AI Agent
6. Fetches revenue analytics
7. Formats structured Markdown revenue dashboards
8. Delivers a complete structured intelligence report

This creates a powerful **Company → Compliance → Revenue → Risk → Opportunity** automation pipeline.

==============================================================================
2. WORKFLOW NODE BREAKDOWN
==========================

Below is the technical breakdown of the nodes used in the n8n workflow, following execution logic.

---

## 🔹 LAYER 1 – ENTRY & ROUTING

1. Webhook (Trigger)

   * Entry point of the system
   * Receives POST request with:

     * OurCompanyName
     * Company Name
     * Company URL
   * Response mode handled by Respond to Webhook nodes

2. Edit Fields

   * Standardizes incoming data
   * Extracts:

     * OurCompanyName
     * CompanyName
     * CompanyURL

3. Switch Node

   * Routes execution based on OurCompanyName
   * Enables multi-brand intelligence mode
   * Supports:

     * MCM
     * AcePeak
     * TechOpenSystem
     * LetsDial
     * SoftTop
     * Teloz
     * Ajoxi
     * Rozper
     * Meratalk
   * Each branch injects brand-specific strategy logic

---

## 🔹 LAYER 2 – COMPANY IDENTITY & REGULATORY DATA

4. CompanyName (LLM Extraction Node)

   * Extracts official company name from URL
   * Removes suffixes like LLC, Inc, Ltd
   * Ensures clean legal entity matching

5. DataExpress (FCC API Lookup)

   * Calls external FCC Search API
   * Retrieves:

     * 499 Filer ID
     * Registration number
     * Legal entity name
     * Headquarters details

6. Code in JavaScript (Data Normalizer)

   * Converts API response into structured JSON
   * Normalizes labels into safe keys
   * Handles duplicate fields
   * Extracts RMD data

7. Edit Fields (Regulatory Mapping)

   * Maps structured fields:

     * 499 Filer ID
     * FRN Number
     * RMD Registration
     * Registration Date
     * Address
     * Contact details

---

## 🔹 LAYER 3 – AI DUE DILIGENCE ENGINE

8. AI Agent (Core Intelligence Engine)

   * Executes a multi-phase telecom due diligence protocol

   PHASE I – Website Discovery

   * Legal names
   * Addresses
   * Incorporation details
   * Technology stack
   * Network footprint
   * Compliance claims

   PHASE II – Data Fusion

   * Cross-checks:

     * FCC Filer ID
     * FRN
     * RMD
     * Registration numbers
   * Flags discrepancies

   PHASE III – Market & Reputation Intelligence

   * LinkedIn
   * Crunchbase
   * Wikipedia
   * Social footprint
   * News (last 24 months)
   * Fraud history
   * Risk analysis

   Outputs structured intelligence including:

   * Company Overview
   * Key Highlights
   * Leadership & Management
   * Compliance & Licenses
   * Risk Level (Low / Moderate / High)
   * Tier Ranking (Tier 1 / Tier 2 / Tier 3)
   * Credit Recommendation
   * Strategic Business Opportunities
   * STIR/SHAKEN analysis

9. OpenRouter Chat Model (Gemini 3 Pro)

   * High-context intelligence processing
   * Handles deep regulatory + market reasoning
   * Ensures structured output

---

## 🔹 LAYER 4 – REVENUE INTELLIGENCE MODULE

10. HTTP Request (Revenue API)

* Calls internal revenue intelligence endpoint
* Retrieves:

  * Revenue summary
  * Top countries
  * Interconnected carriers
  * Last revenue date

11. Revenue (Data Mapping Node)

* Structures revenue response
* Prepares clean input for AI formatting

12. Basic LLM Chain (Revenue Formatter)

* Converts raw revenue data into clean Markdown
* Creates:

  * Revenue Summary Table
  * Country-wise Revenue Table
  * Interconnection Cards
* Removes raw JSON

---

## 🔹 LAYER 5 – DELIVERY

13. Edit Fields (Final Merge Layer)

* Combines:

  * Due Diligence Report
  * Revenue Intelligence Report

14. Respond to Webhook

* Sends final structured report back to frontend
* Enables real-time dashboard rendering

